data.enText: to refuse to accept sth and try to stop it from happening

data.chText: 他们决心顶住要求改革法律的压力。
data.enText: They are determined to resist pressure to change the law.

data.chText: 银行强烈反对降低利率。
data.enText: The bank strongly resisted cutting interest rates.
to fight back when attacked; to use force to stop sth from happening

data.chText: 他试图制伏我，但我奋力反抗。
data.enText: He tried to pin me down, but I resisted.
She was charged with resisting arrest .
to stop yourself from having sth you like or doing sth you very much want to do

data.chText: 我忍不住把整块蛋糕都吃了。
data.enText: I finished the cake. I couldn't resist it .

data.chText: 我抵挡不住逃课的诱惑。
data.enText: I found the temptation to miss the class too hard to resist.

data.chText: 他忍不住炫耀起了他的新车。
data.enText: He couldn't resist showing off his new car.
to not be harmed or damaged by sth

data.chText: 健康饮食有助于身体抗感染。
data.enText: A healthy diet should help your body resist infection.

data.chText: 这种新油漆具有耐热性。
data.enText: This new paint is designed to resist heat.

simple_means.memory_skill: re 相反；反对；不 + sist 站 → 反抗，抵抗

ex.chText: 如果没人反对的话，该计划将立即执行。
ex.enText: If no one objects, the plan will be implemented immediately.

ex.chText: 她坚决反对重建该寺庙。
ex.enText: She strongly objected to rebuilding the temple.

ex.chText: 她不赞成聘用那个男人。
ex.enText: She objected to recruiting that man.

synonyms.bx: 语气强烈，指对某一具体做法、计划等表示反对，常后接介词 to。

ex.chText: 我不反对你的计划。
ex.enText: I have no objection to your plan.

tips.tip: 在表示“不反对…”时，习惯上用 have no objection to，而不用 do not object to。

ex.chText: 经济学家对通货膨胀的原因看法不一。
ex.enText: Economists differ on the cause of inflation.

ex.chText: 他总是与她意见相左。
ex.enText: He always differs with her.

ex.chText: 在这件事上我和你意见不同。
ex.enText: I disagree with you on this matter.

ex.chText: 即便是亲密的朋友有时也有分歧。
ex.enText: Even close friends disagree sometimes.

ex.chText: 有些人不同意他的论点。
ex.enText: Some people disagree with his argument.

synonyms.bx: 指与他人在看法上有分歧，也指不赞同计划、行动等，语气较differ 强烈，常后接介词 with。

ex.chText: 国会会继续反对总统的经济紧缩措施吗？
ex.enText: Will the Congress continue to oppose the President's austerity measures?

ex.chText: 委员会反对改变规则。
ex.enText: The committee opposed changing the regulations.

ex.chText: 当地居民强烈反对这个计划。
ex.enText: The local residents bitterly opposed the scheme.

ex.chText: 我们反对任何外来势力插手干预。
ex.enText: We oppose interference by any outside force.

synonyms.bx: 指不赞同某一政策、计划等，含抵制或阻挠之意。

ex.chText: 成千上万的人走上街头，抗议经济紧缩政策。
ex.enText: Tens of thousands of people took to the streets, protesting against the austerity policy.

ex.chText: 许多学生反对那项决定。
ex.enText: Many students protested the decision.

ex.chText: 数千人抗议新法规。
ex.enText: Thousands of people protested against the new legislation.

ex.chText: “我不明白为什么他会升职！”她抗议道。
ex.enText: 'I don't see why he should get the promotion!' she protested.

synonyms.bx: 通常指人们聚集在一起，以言语、行为等公开表示不满或异议，也可指个人不认同某事或对某事心有不满。

ex.chText: 那位部长顶住了要求其辞职的压力。
ex.enText: The minister resisted pressure to resign.

ex.chText: 为什么该计划遭到董事会的强烈反对？
ex.enText: Why was the plan fiercely resisted by the board?

ex.chText: 该公司拒绝改变聘用制度。
ex.enText: The company resisted changing its recruitment system.

synonyms.bx: 指拒绝作出改变或不屈从于外力而做某事。

example: The mountain climbers had to fend against the ice and snow

tr: stand up or offer resistance to somebody or something
express opposition through action or words
example: dissent to the laws of the country

tr: elude, especially in a baffling way
resist immunologically the introduction of some foreign tissue or organ
example: His body rejected the liver of the donor

value.def: If you resist something such as a change, you refuse to accept it and try to prevent it.

example.ex: She says she will resist a single European currency being imposed...
example.tran: 她说她会反对在欧洲推行单一货币。

example.ex: They resisted our attempts to modernize the distribution of books.
example.tran: 他们反对我们采用现代化方式发行图书。

value.def: If you resist someone or resist an attack by them, you fight back against them.

example.ex: The man was shot outside his house as he tried to resist arrest...
example.tran: 该男子在其住宅外拒捕时被击毙。

example.ex: When she had attempted to cut his nails he resisted.
example.tran: 她试图给他剪指甲，他不让。

value.def: If you resist doing something, or resist the temptation to do it, you stop yourself from doing it although you would like to do it.

example.ex: Students should resist the temptation to focus on exams alone...
example.tran: 学生们应当抵制诱惑，集中精力备考。

example.ex: She cannot resist giving him advice.

value.def: If someone or something resists damage of some kind, they are not damaged.

example.ex: ...bodies trained and toughened to resist the cold...
example.tran: 经过训练和磨炼，可以抵御寒冷的身体

example.ex: Chemicals form a protective layer that resists both oil and water-based stains.
example.tran: 化学物质形成了一个抗油污和水渍的保护层。
